      "content": [
        {
          "type": "story",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "value": "HATBALL"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "At the end of a long day's exhibiting, it's important to start the evening by unwinding with a good few frames of Hatball. So you can all join in at home, here are the official rules of Hatball."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "EQUIPMENT REQUIRED: 1.) One baseball cap 2.) Human beings"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "The bowler (or pitcher, as he or she is known in American Hatball) throws the hat, or 'ball', towards the fielders (receivers in American Hatball)."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "In order to score a Hatball, a competitor must catch the 'ball' (hat) on their head without using their hands. The 'ball' (not really a ball but actually a hat) must land squarely and reasonably straight on the competitor's head in such a way that a passer-by unaware of the game would assume they were simply wearing a hat ('ball')."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Meeting the above criteria is judged as 'scoring one Hatball'."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "No scores are kept in a game of Hatball, nor are there winners or losers. No teams or league tables exist; the game is played purely for the joy of playing. However, those who score a notiecable amount of hatballs are revered and seen as gods. Of Hatball."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "You are now ready to play. Please enjoy yourselves and always remember to Hatball responsibly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
